11.3 Known Reporting Issues
•	LE Control Panel Reports Timeout: For large enterprise merchants, the Gateway makes hundreds of thousands of paginated API requests to Arbiter to generate DFIR and DLR. This can take over the one-hour job limit, causing timeouts and report generation failures. This was a known issue that EPP would not solve short-term — merchants would continue to use SFTP reports as the workaround.
•	SFTP Report Reconciliation Issues: Merchants were using Disputes SFTP reports to infer money movement, but dispute history events were inherently unreliable for financial events because not all financial events are tied to a status change. Uber had 18 different custom SFTP report variants in the US alone — these were owned by the Reporting team and largely invisible to the Disputes/Arbiter team.
•	DFR Coverage Gap: DFR — the long-term replacement for all reconciliation reporting — was only available to 3 merchants as of March 2023 (Uber, Meta, Microsoft). 10 more were in the pipeline. Rolling it out to all EPP Phase 4 merchants was Reporting's responsibility and had no firm ETA for Control Panel extension.
11.4 Reporting Data Contract
Establishing a formal data contract with the Reporting team was a must-have MVP requirement for all EPP phases. The contract defined when dispute data was available for Reporting to generate DFR and DDR, and was part of the broader Funding Handshake discussed in the RFC section. This work was related to the 'Pinless LE Disputes' scope which was scheduled to complete before EPP's MVP launch.
